<tmc-service-paragraph><pub id="RM25T0E"><servcat id="_51"><name>Engine / Hybrid System</name><section id="_057930"><name>CRUISE CONTROL</name><ttl id="_0287962"><name>CRUISE CONTROL SYSTEM</name><para id="RM100000000ZP8O" category="C"><dtccode>P0575</dtccode><dtcname>Cruise Control Input Circuit</dtcname><subpara id="RM100000000ZP8O_01" category="03"><name>DESCRIPTION</name><content5><ptxt>This DTC indicates an abnormality in the ECM.</ptxt><table type="dtc-explan-table" pgwide="1"><tgroup cols="4"><colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.71in"/><colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.71in"/><colspec colname="3" colwidth="3.89in"/><colspec colname="4" colwidth="1.77in"/><thead><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>DTC No.</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Detection Item</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>DTC Detection Condition</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Trouble Area</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-code"><ptxt>P0575</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="detect-item"><ptxt>Cruise Control Input Circuit</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-detect-cond"><ptxt>When either of the following conditions is met:</ptxt><list1 type="unordered"><item><ptxt>Cruise control input signal abnormal</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>ECM internal cancel circuit malfunction</ptxt></item></list1></data-name></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><data-name name="trouble-area"><ptxt>ECM</ptxt></data-name></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><atten4><ptxt>The ECM receives signals from each sensor to control all functions of the cruise control system. When a trouble code is detected, the fail-safe function remains on until the ignition switch is turned off.</ptxt></atten4></content5></subpara><subpara id="RM100000000ZP8O_05" category="01"><name>PROCEDURE</name><testgrp id="RM100000000ZP8O_05_0001" cellposition="1-1"><testtitle>CHECK FOR DTCs</testtitle><content6><test1><ptxt>Connect the GTS to the DLC3.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Turn the ignition switch to ON.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Turn the GTS on.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Clear the DTCs.</ptxt><ptxt>Click here<mlink><xref label="Seep00001" term-id-from="002" href="RM100000000ZP8G"/></mlink></ptxt><gts-info category="dtc-delete"><title>Powertrain &gt; Cruise Control &gt; Clear DTCs</title><gts-exec function-id="50002"><gts-ecu ecu-id="237"/></gts-exec><app-communication><app-param name="process-mode">0</app-param><app-param name="edit-mode">1</app-param><app-param name="insert-mode">0</app-param><app-param name="function-tab">0</app-param><app-param name="category-div">1</app-param><app-param name="category-div-name">Powertrain</app-param><app-param name="ecu-id">237</app-param><app-param name="ecu-name">Cruise Control</app-param><app-param name="gts-order">0</app-param><app-param name="selected-state">1</app-param></app-communication></gts-info></test1><test1><ptxt>Perform the following to make sure that the DTC detection conditions are met.</ptxt><atten4><ptxt>If the detection conditions are not met, the malfunction cannot be detected.</ptxt></atten4></test1><test1><ptxt>Check the DTCs.</ptxt><ptxt>Click here<mlink><xref label="Seep00002" term-id-from="002" href="RM100000000ZP8G"/></mlink></ptxt><gts-info category="dtc-read"><title>Powertrain &gt; Cruise Control &gt; Trouble Codes</title><gts-exec function-id="50001"><gts-ecu ecu-id="237"/></gts-exec><app-communication><app-param name="process-mode">0</app-param><app-param name="edit-mode">1</app-param><app-param name="insert-mode">0</app-param><app-param name="function-tab">0</app-param><app-param name="category-div">1</app-param><app-param name="category-div-name">Powertrain</app-param><app-param name="ecu-id">237</app-param><app-param name="ecu-name">Cruise Control</app-param><app-param name="gts-order">0</app-param>